{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c31627a0-516c-4cc9-83d8-5bd721a149f9","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical order:**  \n`Created → Activated → (Deactivated → Stopped → Resumed → Activated)* → Destroying`\n\n- **Backgrounding** is iOS/Mac Catalyst only (save state before suspension).  \n- **Stopped/Resumed** fire when the app loses/regains focus or goes to the background and back.\n\nReplace `Debug.WriteLine` with your preferred logger (`ILogger`, `Console.WriteLine`, etc.).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9868c0b7-90f9-4614-bf41-fbdd49d7bc4b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question — I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.","outputTokens":398},"id":"b14f480a-3ada-452a-b4e1-282a26003733","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:44:50.871Z","parentId":"c37f7f64-bd7b-4930-a990-cdff39a8d913"}
